data.chText: 使享有权利；使符合资格
data.enText: to give sb the right to have or to do sth

data.chText: 你到65岁就有资格享受养老金。
data.enText: You will be entitled to your pension when you reach 65.

data.chText: 人人都有权发表自己的意见。
data.enText: Everyone's entitled to their own opinion.

data.chText: 你拿这张票不能坐头等舱。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: This ticket does not entitle you to travel first class.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: to give a title to a book, play, etc.

data.chText: 他朗诵一首题为《盐》的诗。

tr: make someone a member of the nobility

example: The Freedom of Information Act entitles you to request your FBI file

value.def: If you are entitled to something, you have the right to have it or do it.

example.ex: If the warranty is limited, the terms may entitle you to a replacement or refund...
example.tran: 如果保修有限制，根据条款你也许可以要求退换或者退款。

example.ex: They are entitled to first class travel...
example.tran: 他们可以坐头等舱旅行。

example.ex: There are 23 Clubs throughout the U.S., and your membership entitles you to enjoy all of them.
example.tran: 全美共有23家俱乐部，您的会员资格可让您享受所有俱乐部的服务。

value.def: If the title of something such as a book, film, or painting is, for example, 'Sunrise', you can say that it is entitled 'Sunrise'.

example.ex: Chomsky's review is entitled 'Psychology and Ideology'.
example.tran: 乔姆斯基的这篇评论题为《心理学与意识形态》。

value.tran: 给（书、电影、绘画等）命名；给…题名
